"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. Albert Howard's book, Gardening or Farming, Gardening and Farming for Health or Disease, a more elegant tile of soil and health that was later come up they came up with, is all about how the birthright of plants is health. That the reason why plants will start to deteriorate while they succumb to disease and pestilence is because of soil quality. When you deplete the soil of its organic matter, when there's a soil uh when the drainage isn't proper, when there's a an acute uh accumulation of water which so uh deprives the soil of its oxygen, this is when you start to get pestilence and disease. Well-made soil, healthy soil will produce healthy plants. And yes, there will be some bugs here and there, but it won't overwhelm the plant. There might be uh some deterioration in some bottom leaves or some natural problems with uh a small percentage of the plant, but the overall plant is healthy. And this is because the soil provides the microbes that feed the plant and provide its protection from all the different things that will consume it and and take away its health. And so it's the it's the basis of regenerative agriculture, that organic matter must be returned to the soil for it to be active, healthy soil. And when you do production farming, production agriculture, you tend to take more organic matter out of the soil than put back in because you harvest the plants. You take the plants off of the soil. And nowadays you till it and you uh sow it with fertilizers and pesticides and you do all these things, but you don't have to do those things, and eventually nature is going to figure this out as going to come for those plants because those aren't healthy plants. You need living matter in the soil to create healthy plants, and from this, all the diseases and pestilence that commercial crops experience will be managed, will be fixed, will be eradicated. And he showed this. He went over, I think a 20 to 30 year period all across the world, from India to South Africa to Europe to the Americas, looking at major commercial crops, documenting them, and analyzing what the pestilence that these people were dealing with. You know, was it uh worms or was it uh you know caterpillars or was it a disease of some sort? And through um analyzing the soil, making sure that it was properly draining and then adding humans, adding organic matter to it, he was he was able to completely eradicate these problems within a two year span in every single crop. This is the system. This is regenerative agriculture. This is how it works. You return organ organic matter to the soil that you've taken out through production crops. And this is how we can gain long-term health because it the trajectory of our modern farming system is not good. Eventually these systems will break down already it's breaking our water systems. Soon we're gonna have pestilence and disease that we can't manage. And right now we eradicate all life in the soil to get after that pestilence and disease. We attack the pestilence as a disease as opposed to fortifying the plant. We need to turn this around before it's too late. Anyway thanks y'all\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 1.28,\n      \"duration\": 0.96,\n      \"confidence\": 0.976,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.948\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.72,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.88,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n 